## TRIPLE GAP ANALYSIS (2026-06-12) — Senior Dev / Architect / QA
Third review pass: what is MISSING (gaps, not bugs). Numbered G*.
Does not repeat AR/CR/DX. The same-day best-practice fixes (0 audit
vulnerabilities, core lint gate, package metadata, CONTRIBUTING.md) are in DONE.

### Senior Dev — missing capabilities in the code
- [ ] **G1. OAuth 2.0 auth** — Basic auth only; instances with SSO/MFA policies
      cannot use the CLI/MCP. Minimum: OAuth password grant + refresh token in the
      credential store.
- [x] **G2. Schema validation for sync.config.js** — DONE 2026-06-12:
      validateConfigShape in config.ts (no new dependency) — wrong type = hard
      error, unknown key = warning listing the valid options; 4 new tests
      (configValidation.test.ts).
- [ ] **G3. Download progress/resume** — push has checkpoint/resume and a progress
      bar; downloading a large scope has neither (a network failure means starting
      over).
- [x] **G4. Rate-limit awareness in the MCP client** — DONE 2026-06-12: shared
      MAX_REQUESTS_PER_SECOND=20 constant in sn-transport; the mcp client spaces
      requests (acquireRequestSlot, min 50ms interval) instead of relying only on
      429 retries.
- [x] **G5. Typed CLI args** — DONE 2026-06-12: typedHandler<TArgs> helper in
      cliCommands.ts — handler bodies are type-checked against TArgs; the 16
      scattered `as unknown as` casts were replaced with one controlled bridge.
      (Full InferredOptionTypes derivation from the options declarations remains a
      possible follow-up.)

### Architect — missing infrastructure
- [ ] **G6. Release automation** — no changesets/semantic-release; versions are
      bumped manually (lerna fixed mode), CHANGELOG.md is static. A single
      `npx changeset` solves the version+changelog+publish sequence.
- [ ] **G7. CLI diagnostics telemetry** — MCP has metrics/audit; the CLI has
      nothing (doctor is a snapshot). An opt-in local diagnostic log
      (~/.syncrona/logs) would shorten the support cycle.
- [x] **G8. Plugin API contract** — DONE 2026-06-13: pluginContract.test.ts pins
      the public plugin contract on two layers — (1) a `referencePlugin` typed
      against `Sync.Plugin`/`PluginFunc`/`FileContext` so an incompatible
      interface change fails to COMPILE, and (2) a conforming plugin loaded
      through the real PluginManager from <rootDir>/node_modules/<name>,
      asserting call shape, output chaining, first-match rule selection, and
      short-circuit on success:false. 4 tests. Related to DX13.
- [ ] **G9. Proxy/TLS configuration** — corporate proxies and self-signed
      certificates are not supported/documented in either HTTP client
      (HTTPS_PROXY env, custom CA bundle).
- [ ] **G10. Machine-enforced module boundaries** — the ARCHITECTURE §5 contract
      (handlers don't import index, sn-transport stays pure, etc.) is not checked
      by anything. dependency-cruiser or eslint-plugin-boundaries in the lint gate.

### QA — missing test coverage
- [x] **G11. E2E against an instance** — DONE 2026-06-12 (local slices):
      e2eCliSmoke.test.ts runs the real dist binary as a child process
      (packaging/bootstrap breakage), and e2eNetworkSmoke.test.ts drives the
      REAL snClient (axios, basic auth, rate limiter) over actual sockets
      against a mock SN Table API — download (manifest build) and push
      (PATCH) slices, auth header asserted on the wire. Optional follow-up:
      record-replay against a live instance (needs credentials; see CR22).
- [x] **G12. Branch coverage for mcp-server** — DONE 2026-06-12:
      check-coverage-gate.js accepts --branch-threshold (opt-in); root
      test:coverage:mcp uses 70 (measured 74.99%).
- [ ] **G13. Mutation testing** — Stryker on credential-store + sn-transport
      (small, critical packages) would show whether the assertions actually guard.
- [ ] **G14. Performance baseline** — no benchmark (manifest build over N tables,
      push of N files); speed regressions are invisible. A single `npm run bench`
      with a fixed dataset + threshold in CI.
- [x] **G15. OS matrix in CI** — DONE 2026-06-13: live CI is now
      .github/workflows/ci.yml (the repo lives on GitHub; azure-pipelines.yml
      does not run there), matrix ubuntu-latest + macos-latest, Node from
      .nvmrc, full check chain. Windows remains with D5/DX1.
- [ ] **G16. Security automation in CI** — PARTIAL: `npm audit --omit=dev
      --audit-level=high` is a CI step in both azure-pipelines.yml and the
      GitHub Actions workflow (verified locally: 0 vulnerabilities). Remaining:
      secret scanning (gitleaks) — requires an external tool in the pipeline.
- [x] **G17. Tests must not dirty the tracked tree** — DONE 2026-06-13: the
      culprit was commandsDownload.test.ts — downloadCommand calls the REAL
      generateScopeDocs(man), which resolves its outDir from process.cwd() and
      so rewrote packages/core/docs/scopes/x_test.md (cwd = packages/core under
      jest) with a fresh timestamp every run. Fixed by stubbing ../scopeDocs in
      that test (the test is about download orchestration, not doc generation).
      Verified: full core suite leaves the tracked tree clean.

### Recommended order (G)
1. ~~G16 + G15~~ done (G16 without gitleaks; G15 now on GitHub Actions, no Windows).
2. ~~G2~~, ~~G5~~, ~~G8~~, ~~G11~~ done.
3. G1 (OAuth) + G9 (proxy) — unlock enterprise use; plan together with D5.
4. G6/G7/G10, G13–G14, G17 — incrementally. (~~G12~~, ~~G4~~ done.)

