## FULL REVIEW (2026-06-13) — architect / dev / qa pass
Fresh three-persona pass over the current tree (does not repeat AR/CR/DX/G).
Findings prefixed ARCH-/DEV-/QA-.

### Architect
- [x] **ARCH-1. Duplicated `ToolResponse` type (12 copies)** — DONE 2026-06-13:
      the identical `{ isError; content: Array<{type;text}> }` shape was
      copy-pasted in all 11 mcp-server handlers plus `ToolHandlerResponse` in
      toolDispatch.ts — a silent drift surface. Consolidated into a leaf module
      `toolResponse.ts`; handlers import it, `ToolHandlerResponse` is now an
      alias. typecheck + lint green.
- [x] **ARCH-2. Other intra-mcp duplicated types** — DONE 2026-06-13: handlers
      now `import type` the canonical definitions — GraphNode/GraphEdge from
      analysis/graph.ts (3 handlers), CmdResult from processRunner (runtimeUtils
      + workspaceHandlers), UnifiedTaskType exported from toolService and
      imported by workflowHandlers. Each type has exactly one definition now;
      `import type` is erased at compile so zero runtime/cycle risk. check green.
- Confirmed healthy (no action): invariants #1 (no stdout pollution) and #2
  (both clients consume sn-transport for prefix/retry/endpoint-not-found, incl.
  CR18) hold; no cyclic/upward imports; handlers don't import index (§5). The
  only documented structural gaps remain AR11 (module-level mutable state) and
  G10 (boundaries not machine-enforced) — both design-level, left as tracked.

### Dev
- [~] **DEV-1. No-op `catch (e) { throw e; }` blocks (12 sites)** — these wrap a
      body in try/catch only to re-throw the same error: dead structure that
      obscures which code actually has error handling. FIXED the 3 in
      PluginManager.ts (clean rewrite, behavior identical, core suite green).
      REMAINING 9 DEFERRED (commands.ts:177/211/302, appUtils.ts:277/595/705,
      wizard.ts:212/225, FileUtils.ts:296): each wraps a whole function body, so
      removal means de-indenting large bodies — a big diff with real risk for
      ZERO behavior change. Per the review rule (don't fix mechanically-risky
      noise), left as-is intentionally. Reopen only if touching those functions
      for another reason.
- [ ] **DEV-2. `allSettled` reinvents native `Promise.allSettled`** —
      genericUtils.ts `allSettled` returns `{status:"fulfilled",value}` /
      `{status:"rejected",reason}`, which is exactly the native
      `Promise.allSettled` result shape (available on Node 22). Replace the
      custom helper with the native call and drop `Sync.PromiseResult`. Minor;
      no bug, just dead reimplementation.
- No correctness/async/resource defects found beyond the above — the CR1–CR30
  series already covered the real bugs (push state, retry policy, swallowed
  errors, manifest data loss).

### QA
- [x] **QA-1. Broken-config hard-fail was untested (invariant #6 / CR20)** —
      DONE 2026-06-13: config.ts throws "Failed to load config file" on a
      present-but-broken sync.config.js (never silently DEFAULT_CONFIG), but no
      test locked it — a refactor could quietly restore the dangerous default
      fallback. Added a regression test (syntactically broken config → rejects)
      to configValidation.test.ts. 5/5 green.
- [ ] **QA-2. Thin handler coverage** — 5 mcp test files for 11 handlers; mcp
      tests run against compiled `dist/` not `src/` (AR9, known). Adding
      per-handler tests against dist is the path; tracked, not done here.
- [ ] **QA-3. Single-file `npx jest <file>` from repo root falls back to babel
      and fails to parse TS** (`as` casts) — ts-jest only applies when run from
      packages/core or via `npm --workspace @syncrona/core test`. Contributor
      gotcha; document in CONTRIBUTING or add a root jest config. Minor.

